  "title": "docs(widgets): Use primitive types instead of wrappers",
  "body": "Used this script to automatically do it:\n\n``` sh\n#! /usr/bin/bash\n\nfor wrapper in String Number Boolean; do\n  prim=`echo $wrapper | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]'`\n  for file in `echo README.md widgets/*/*.js`; do\n    for i in `seq 3`; do\n      sed -i -r \"s/(@param.*)(${wrapper})/\\1${prim}/g\" $file\n    done\n  done\ndone\n```\n\nI think it should have gotten all of them. Maybe you can think of some other places than on the `@param` lines where we should replace them?\n",
